{"title":"Module Bundling - Stencil","description":"Module Bundling","url":"/docs/module-bundling","contributors":["jthoms1","adamdbradley","kensodemann","manucorporat","ryan3E0"],"headings":[{"id":"module-bundling","level":1,"text":"Module Bundling"},{"id":"one-component-per-module","level":2,"text":"One Component Per Module"},{"id":"commonjs-dependencies","level":2,"text":"CommonJS Dependencies"},{"id":"namedmodules-x-is-not-exported-by-x","level":3,"text":"NamedModules: X is not exported by X"},{"id":"custom-rollup-plugins","level":2,"text":"Custom Rollup plugins"},{"id":"node-polyfills","level":2,"text":"Node Polyfills"},{"id":"1-install-rollup-plugin-node-polyfills","level":3,"text":"1. Install <code>rollup-plugin-node-polyfills</code>:"},{"id":"2-update-the-stencil-config-ts-file-including-the-plugin","level":3,"text":"2. Update the <code>stencil.config.ts</code> file including the plugin:"},{"id":"strict-mode","level":2,"text":"Strict Mode"}],"srcPath":"./src/docs/guides/module-bundling.md","hypertext":["div",null,["h1",{"id":"module-bundling"},"\n  \n  Module Bundling\n  \n"],"\n",["p",null,"Stencil uses ",["a",{"href":"https://rollupjs.org/guide/en/"},"Rollup"]," under the hood to bundle your components. This guide will explain and recommend certain workarounds for some of the most common bundling issues you might encounter."],"\n\n",["h2",{"id":"one-component-per-module"},"\n  ",["a",{"class":"heading-link","href":"#one-component-per-module"},["app-icon",{"name":"link"}],"\n  One Component Per Module\n  "],"\n"],"\n",["p",null,"For Stencil to bundle your components most efficiently, you must declare a single component (class decorated with ",["code",null,"@Component"],") per ",["em",null,"TypeScript"]," file, and the component itself ",["strong",null,"must"]," have a unique ",["code",null,"export"],". By doing so, Stencil is able to easily analyze the entire component graph within the app, and best understand how components should be bundled together. Under-the-hood it uses the Rollup bundler to efficiently bundled shared code together. Additionally, lazy-loading is a default feature of Stencil, so code-splitting is already happening automatically, and only dynamically importing components which are being used on the page."],"\n",["p",null,"Modules that contain a component are entry-points, which means that no other module should import anything from them."],"\n",["p",null,"The following example is ",["strong",null,"NOT"]," valid:"],"\n",["p",null,["strong",null,"src/components/my-cmp.tsx:"]],"\n\n  ",["highlight-code",null,"\n    ",["pre",{"class":"language-tsx"},["code",{"class":"language-tsx"},["span",{"class":"token comment"},"// This module has a component, you cannot export anything else"],"\n",["span",{"class":"token keyword"},"export"]," ",["span",{"class":"token keyword"},"function"]," ",["span",{"class":"token function"},"someUtilFunction"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"("],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},")"]," ",["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"{"],"\n  ",["span",{"class":"token builtin"},"console"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"."],["span",{"class":"token function"},"log"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"("],["span",{"class":"token string"},"'do stuff'"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},")"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},";"],"\n",["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"}"],"\n\n@",["span",{"class":"token function"},"Component"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"("],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"{"],"\n  tag",["span",{"class":"token operator"},":"]," ",["span",{"class":"token string"},"'my-cmp'"],"\n",["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"}"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},")"],"\n",["span",{"class":"token keyword"},"export"]," ",["span",{"class":"token keyword"},"class"]," ",["span",{"class":"token class-name"},"MyCmp"]," ",["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"{"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"}"]]],"\n  "],"\n  ",["p",nul